<legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="County Government And Officers" statutenumber="23-1115"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>23-1115</statuteno><catchline>County officers; deputies; compensation.</catchline><para>When a county officer is compelled by the pressure of the business of the office to employ a deputy, the county commissioners may make a reasonable allowance to such a deputy.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>R.S.1866, c. 15, &#167; 6, p. 128; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 5742; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 5071; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 84-808; </para><para>R.S.1943, (1987), &#167; 84-808; </para><para>Laws 1990, LB 821, &#167; 2. </para></source></law></legaldoc>